	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Build the Cradle</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-97" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-1024x682.jpg" alt="11b_DSC07442" width="730" height="486" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a>The finished cradle in all its glory.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/9_DSC07375.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-94" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/9_DSC07375-1024x682.jpg" alt="9_DSC07375" width="730" height="486" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/9_DSC07375-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/9_DSC07375-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/9_DSC07375-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/9_DSC07375-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a> Prepare a 50mm M8 Bolt by adding a flange bearing and then a washer. Insert a cross dowel into a Cradle Base dowel hole. Line up the slot on the dowel head with the corresponding bolt hole. Insert the prepared M8 Bolt. It might be a little tricky to start. Tighten a quarter turn past finger tight. Repeat to add the other three bearings to the base. If the Cradle Base rests unevenly like an old restaurant table, just loosen the bolts, sit the base on a level surface, and retighten.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/10a_DSC07404.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-95" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/10a_DSC07404-1024x682.jpg" alt="10a_DSC07404" width="730" height="486" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/10a_DSC07404-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/10a_DSC07404-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/10a_DSC07404-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/10a_DSC07404-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a> Fit the Cradle Angles into the Cradle Leaves as pictured. The tabs on the Angles should face inside, toward each other.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-98" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC07410-1024x682.jpg" alt="DSC07410" width="730" height="486" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC07410-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC07410-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC07410-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/DSC07410-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a> Hammer the Cradle Angles to fully seat them. You can be pretty forceful, don&#8217;t worry. Works best with a deadblow hammer or frozen ham.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-96" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424-1024x682.jpg" alt="11a_DSC07424" width="730" height="486" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11a_DSC07424-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a> Insert the bicycle skewers through the holes on the Cradle Angles. Tighten the nuts on the bicycle skewers. Clamp.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-97" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-1024x682.jpg" alt="11b_DSC07442" width="730" height="486" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/11b_DSC07442-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a> Seat the finished Leaves and Angles into the Cradle Base slots, making a V shape. For easy use, you want the skewer clamps to face the front of the scanner. Adjust the clamps until the whole cradle feels sturdy. Now you can easily unclamp and slide to fit any book spines.</p>
<p><a href="index028b.html@page_id=52">Next&#8230; Build the Imaging Module!</a> </p>
